        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          Carnatic ragas form the foundation of South Indian classical music, with 72 melakarta (parent) ragas 
          and numerous janya (derived) ragas. Each raga has specific ascending (arohana) and descending (avarohana) scales.
        </p>
